<http://identifiers.org/rgd/632280>
        a       owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1710  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Neurabin is a known actin-binding protein (see Additional literature and others).\nFig. 3: Expression of GFPNrbI(1-287) Increases Spine Length and Density\nFig. 4: Actin Binding Domain of NrbI Is Sufficient for Spine Morphogenesis\nFig. 5: GFP-NrbI(1-287) Causes Actin Polymerization\nFig. 8. Spines Expressing GFPNrbI(1-287) Exhibited Increased Motility\n\nTogether this shows that neurabin is a regulator of postsynaptic actin structure. Since there is no real mentioning of a stimulus, I chose the more general term 'postsynaptic actin cytoskeleton organization (GO:0098974)' rather than 'regulation of modification of postsynaptic actin cytoskeleton (GO:1905274)'. Experimental description: - Rat neurons are used: \"Hippocampal slices were prepared from P6 or P7 rats as described\"\n- Species of overexpressed Neurabin 1 traced back to PMID:12052877 \"...were generated by PCR with full-length rat NrbI cDNA as template \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1710" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

